# Linear Project Management

- Treat Linear as the source of truth for product scope, issue status, acceptance criteria, blockers, and delegation notes.
- When the user asks to manage work, prefer updating Linear over writing informal chat-only plans.
- Do not create implementation tasks from design tasks until the product owner approves the design/proposal.
- Keep implementation work delegated from specific Linear issues; update issue status before and after delegated work.
- Use `Todo` for not-started work, `In Progress` for active management or implementation, and `Done` only after acceptance criteria are verified.
- Add clear acceptance criteria to every task before assigning or delegating it.
- Do not commit, push, or create PRs unless the user explicitly asks.
